# Aquaculture Water Quality Dashboard - Project Rules

## File Organization
- All configuration files go in `lib/` (wqi-config.ts, recommendation-rules.ts)
- All API routes go in `app/api/`
- All React components go in `components/`
- All TypeScript types go in `types/`
- Mock data goes in `data/`

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all logic files (.ts)
- Use .tsx only for React components
- Keep functions small and focused
- Export configs as const objects for easy modification

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (WQIGauge.tsx)
- Utilities: camelCase (wqi-calculator.ts)
- Config files: kebab-case (wqi-config.ts)
- API routes: kebab-case (sensor-data/route.ts)

## Key Principles
- Keep WQI weights configurable in lib/wqi-config.ts
- Keep recommendation rules configurable in lib/recommendation-rules.ts
- Use rule-based logic (if-then statements), not ML for prototype
- Mobile-first responsive design for farmers in field

